<blockquote>

<b class="c2"><small>Using the Online Help</small></b>
<table width="90%" border="0" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
<td><small>
Online help is shown in a browser window with three separate frames. The toolbar frame on the top
contains buttons with functions described below. On the left, there is a navigation frame with the help
topics. The help topics can be shown as a tree structure or as an alphabetically sorted index list.
The content frame to the right shows the actual help information for chosen topics.
</small></td>
</tr>
</table>

<br />
<b class="c2"><small>Resizing the Browser Frames</small></b>
<table width="90%" border="0" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
<td><small>
Position the cursor on the vertical border (the cursor shape changes).
Click and drag the frame border to a new position.
</small></td>
</tr>
</table>

<br />
<b class="c2"><small>Using the Toolbar Buttons</small></b>
<table width="90%" border="0" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
<td valign="top" width="70"><img border="0" src="search.gif" alt="" /></td>
<td>
<small>
Search help contents for a matching string.
<br />Enter a search string in the search input field and press the <i>Enter</i> key or click the
<i>Search</i> button to start a full text search. Search is always performed on all topics starting from
the first one. All search hits found under a topic are highlighted with <span class="search-hit">orange</span>
background color. The search is <u>not</u> case sensitive. Repeat the search to view the next topic that contains
search hits.
</small></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top" width="70"><img border="0" src="searchnext.gif" alt="" /></td>
<td><small>Go to the next topic that contains search hits.</small></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top" width="70"><img border="0" src="prev.gif" alt="" /></td>
<td><small>Go back to the previously shown topic.</small></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign="top" width="70"><img border="0" src="next.gif" alt="" /></td>
<td><small>Go forward to the next topic.</small></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign="top" width="70"><img border="0" src="tree_view.gif" alt="" /></td>
<td>
<small>Switch to tree view.
<br />Help topics are shown in a tree structure in the navigation frame.
Click the (+) and (-) icons to expand and collapse the tree. Click a topic title
or icon to view the topic content.
<br />A selected topic can contain sub topics shown together in the content frame.  Thus, to view all help topics,
select the root topic in the tree. This is useful, for instance, to simultaneously view more than a single help topic or
to make a printout of selected parts, or of the complete help information.
</small>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign="top" width="70"><img border="0" src="index_view.gif" alt="" /></td>
<td><small>Switch to index view.
<br />The help index consists of an alphabetically ordered list of topic titles shown in
the navigation frame. Click a topic title to show the desired topic content.
</small></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign="top" width="70"><img border="0" src="pdf.gif" alt="" /></td>
<td><small>Show help set in PDF.
<br />
Open the help set as a complete PDF document for high quality printouts, if this button is available.
</small></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign="top" width="70"><img border="0" src="print.gif" alt="" /></td>
<td><small>Print the help topic content currently shown in this frame.
</small></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign="top" width="70"><img border="0" src="help.gif" alt="" /></td>
<td><small>Show this help page.</small></td>
</tr>
</table>

